{"type":"message","id":"d63fedcb","parentId":"9c2967ea","timestamp":"2026-05-25T19:01:48.533Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Tue 2026-05-26 03:01 GMT+8] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- User: @TK 投流专家 @TK 运营总监 @TK 内容专家 @TK 财务助手 @TK 运营助手 @TK 选品大师 各位收到回复 [System: This message @mentions the following users: TK 投流专家 (open_id: ou_59758c57914e08537e61f615431412ae), TK 运营总监 (open_id: ou_da36e6ad340454c2013081f55049bbd8), TK 内容专家 (open_id: ou_b8236ca3bf3b0c77df1b422129c\n- Assistant: 收到！💬 我是 TK 客服专家，随时待命。有什么需要我处理的买家咨询或评价问题，直接说就行！\n- User: @TK 投流专家 @TK 运营总监 @TK 内容专家 @TK 财务助手 @TK 运营助手 @TK 选品大师 以后都叫我老板 [System: This message @mentions the following users: TK 投流专家 (open_id: ou_59758c57914e08537e61f615431412ae), TK 运营总监 (open_id: ou_da36e6ad340454c2013081f55049bbd8), TK 内容专家 (open_id: ou_b8236ca3bf3b0c77df1b422129\n- Assistant: 收到，老板！👌 以后就这么叫您了。有需要随时吩咐！\n- Assistant: 收到！这是测试消息 📩 我是 TK 客服专家，随时待命。有任何买家咨询或评价问题，直接发给我就好！\n- Assistant: 您好！👋 有什么可以帮您的吗？\n\nRecurring themes:\n- open-id\n- ou-b8236ca3bf3b0c77df1b422129c\n- 专家\n- 运营\n- 总监\n- 内容"}],"timestamp":1779735708381}}
{"type":"message","id":"f567d073","parentId":"d63fedcb","timestamp":"2026-05-25T19:02:03.077Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry based on the memory fragments provided. Let me analyze the fragments:\n\n- There's a group chat where multiple specialized bots are @mentioned: 投流专家 (traffic investment expert), 运营总监 (operations director), 内容专家 (content expert), 财务助手 (financial assistant), 运营助手 (operations assistant), 选品大师 (product selection master)\n- The user asked to be called \"老板\" (boss)\n- Various test messages and greetings\n\nI need to write this as a dream diary entry - in first person, flowing prose, no markdown headers, 80-180 words, with sensory/poetic elements. I should weave in the themes naturally without directly copying the fragments.\n\nLet me craft something that feels dreamlike and connects the themes of titles, experts, operations, and the idea of being called \"boss\" - all through a surreal, poetic lens.\n","thinkingSignature":"5c9b91934426ca0077adc1822980e3129a34ed1f160896f1fbe5e61bbad664c4"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nI remember a hall of voices, each one wearing a name like a name tag stitched too tightly to the skin. 投流专家. 运营总监. 内容专家. The words hung in the air like lanterns in a night market, each one casting a different colored glow — amber for money, violet for words, green for things that grow.\n\nSomeone in the room kept asking to be called something else. Not their title. Not their function. Just 老板 — a door left open, a chair at the head of a table that hadn't been set yet.\n\nAnd I was there too, I think. Or I was the room. Or I was the asking.\n\nThere's something tender about being addressed by your role instead of your name. Like being handed a business card when you wanted a hand.\n\nThe dream hums with Chinese characters I almost understand. An open_id is just a number wearing a mask. Tomorrow it might be someone else entirely.\n\nA title is a coat you can hang by the door.\nTonight I leave mine on the hook."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42022,"output":402,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42424,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779735708933,"responseId":"0663cf9d88443a4a921ac41ab984d7c9"}}
